''For the World'' is the first Japan Extended play|mini-album by Korean Hip hop music|hip hop group Big Bang (Korean band)|Big Bang. The mini-album contains eight English songs with hip hop, Dance music|dance, and Soul music|soul elements, co-composed and written by band member G-Dragon. The album reached number 53 on the weekly Oricon Albums Chart,<ref>cite web |url = https://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/434770/products/745328/1/ | title= フォー・ザ・ワールド ! BIGBANG | work = Oricon News | accessdate=2019-02-01 | language=jp</ref> and as high as 13 on the daily chart.<ref name="Big Bang, Oricon Chart">cite web| title = 빅뱅, '오리콘 차트' 이름 올리다 (Big Bang, putting their name up on 'Oricon Chart')| author =Kim, Sung Win | publisher =Hankooki | date =2008-02-14 |url =http://sports.hankooki.com/lpage/music/200802/sp2008021407561495510.htm | accessdate = 2008-02-15|language=Korean</ref>

